          From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia                            Jump to:     navigation,      search            Ek Thi Rani Aisi Bhi      Directed by Gulbahar Singh   Produced by Rajmata Vijayaraje Scindia Smirit Trust   Story by Mridula Sinha   Based on Ek Thi Rani Aisi Bhi   by Mridula Sinha   Starring Hema Malini Sachin Khedekar Vinod Khanna Anjan Srivastava   Music by Monty Sharma    Release dates     1 April 2013 (2013-04-01)       [1]   Country India   Language Hindi   Ek Thi Rani Aisi Bhi is a 2013 Hindi language historical drama/biopic directed by Gul Bahar Singh and starring Indian MP and actress Hema Malini who portrays Vijaya Raje Scindia.[2] The film is based on Mridula Sinha's biography of Scindhia, the former Rajmata of Gwalior, "and her journey from one of the highest aristocrats of the land to a well-known political personality".[3] The film was completed and screened as early as 2008,[2] but theatrical release was put on hold. It was then scheduled for release in 2009,[4] 2010,[3] and 2011,[5] but release was delayed in each case. The movie was finally released on 1 April 2013. References[edit]   ^ Ek Thi Rani Aisi Bhi at movies.com.pk ^ a b Hema Malini takes on Rajmata Vijayaraje Scindhia at rediff.com ^ a b movietalkies.com ^ nowrunning.com ^ "Ek Thi Rani Aisi Bhi". Bollywood Hungama. Retrieved 9 June 2014.        This article about a Hindi film of the 2010s is a stub. You can help Wikipedia by expanding it.   v t e                         Retrieved from "https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Ek_Thi_Rani_Aisi_Bhi&oldid=713609563"          Categories: 2013 filmsHindi-language filmsIndian films2010s Hindi-language films2010s Hindi-language film stubsHidden categories: Use dmy dates from June 2014All stub articles            
